---
template_id: openagreements-restrictive-covenant-new-mexico
name: OpenAgreements Employee Restrictive Covenant (New Mexico)
category: non-compete
description: >-
  New Mexico-specific employee restrictive covenant agreement built for the
  Lovelace / McGonigle common-law reasonableness standard and the health-care
  practitioner statute (NMSA 1978, §§ 24A-4-1 to 24A-4-5): confidentiality and
  trade-secret protection tied to a specific legitimate interest, an employee
  non-solicitation covenant, a customer non-solicitation covenant, and an
  optional non-compete drawn to reasonableness in time, geography, and scope
  rather than copied from a form. The agreement documents independent new
  consideration for a covenant signed after employment begins, because New
  Mexico treats continued at-will employment as illusory (Piano). It excludes
  non-competes for the ten covered health-care practitioner classes, holds the
  surviving practitioner fallbacks — one-year patient and employee non-solicits,
  early-departure repayment, NDAs, and reasonable liquidated damages — within
  their statutory bounds, keeps New Mexico law and a New Mexico forum for
  agreements covering clinical health-care services rendered in the state, and
  secures narrowing through an express reformation clause because New Mexico's
  only staged reformation authority is contract-based (KidsKare). Drafted as a
  starting point for licensed counsel review.
source_url: >-
  https://github.com/open-agreements/open-agreements/tree/main/templates/openagreements-restrictive-covenant-new-mexico
version: 0.1.0
license: CC-BY-4.0
allow_derivatives: true
distribution: bundled
artifact_type: template
attribution_text: >-
  Authored by OpenAgreements contributors. New Mexico-specific analysis informed
  by the quote-verified New Mexico practice note. Licensed under CC BY 4.0.
layout_id: cover-standard-signature-v1
style_id: openagreements-default-v1
document:
  title: Employee Restrictive Covenant Agreement
  label: OpenAgreements Employee Restrictive Covenant (New Mexico)
  version: 0.1.0
  license: Free to use under CC BY 4.0
  include_cloud_doc_line: true
  defined_term_highlight_mode: definition_site_only
  cover_row_height: 317
sections:
