fields:
  - name: employer_name
    type: string
    description: Legal name of the employer
    display_label: Employer
    section: Parties
  - name: employer_signatory_name
    type: string
    description: Full name of the authorized signatory signing for the employer
    display_label: Employer Signatory Name
    section: Parties
  - name: employer_signatory_title
    type: string
    description: Title of the authorized signatory signing for the employer
    display_label: Employer Signatory Title
    section: Parties
  - name: employee_name
    type: string
    description: Full legal name of the employee
    display_label: Employee
    section: Parties
  - name: employee_title
    type: string
    description: Employee job title or position (optional)
    display_label: Employee Title / Position
    default: ''
    section: Parties
  - name: effective_date
    type: date
    description: >-
      Effective date of this agreement. The execution date does statutory work
      in New Mexico: for psychologists, physician assistants, and pharmacists,
      the health-care practitioner article applies only to agreements, renewals,
      or extensions executed on or after the effective date of the 2023 act.
    display_label: Effective Date
    section: Timing
    rationale_source: legislation
    requirement_id: REQ-labor-and-employment-law.restrictive-covenant-agreement.new-mexico.exclude-non-competes-for-covered-health-care-practitioners
  - name: covenant_timing
    type: string
    description: >-
      Whether this agreement is signed as a condition of the initial offer of
      employment or after employment has already begun. New Mexico treats
      continued at-will employment as an illusory promise that cannot be
      consideration, so a mid-stream covenant must be supported by independent
      new consideration.
    display_label: Covenant Timing
    default: at the outset of employment as a condition of the offer
    section: Timing
    default_value_rationale: >-
      For a covenant signed as a condition of initial hire, the offer of
      employment itself can serve as consideration. Replace this with a
      description tied to the new consideration (raise, bonus, promotion, or
      equity grant) when the covenant is signed after employment began.
    rationale_source: case_law
    requirement_id: REQ-labor-and-employment-law.restrictive-covenant-agreement.new-mexico.require-independent-consideration-for-midstream-covenants
  - name: independent_consideration
    type: string
    description: >-
      The bargained-for benefit that supports this agreement. For a mid-stream
      covenant, describe the new consideration (a raise, bonus, promotion,
      equity grant, or other benefit) dated to signing, because a bare recital
      of continued at-will employment is illusory under New Mexico law.
    display_label: Consideration
    default: the offer of employment and Employee's access to Employer's Protected Interests
    section: Timing
    default_value_rationale: >-
      For an at-hire covenant the offer of employment supplies consideration.
      For a covenant signed after employment began, replace this with the
      specific new benefit exchanged for the covenant.
  - name: governing_law
    type: string
    description: >-
      Governing law state. For an agreement covering clinical health-care
      services to be rendered in New Mexico, a provision choosing another
      state's law is void, unenforceable, and against public policy, so this
      should remain New Mexico for such an agreement.
    display_label: Governing Law
    section: Legal
    default: New Mexico
    rationale_source: legislation
    requirement_id: REQ-labor-and-employment-law.restrictive-covenant-agreement.new-mexico.keep-clinical-health-care-agreements-under-new-mexico-law-and-forum
  - name: venue
    type: string
    description: >-
      Forum for disputes. For an agreement covering clinical health-care
      services rendered in New Mexico, a provision requiring litigation in
      another state is void, so the forum should remain New Mexico for such an
      agreement.
    display_label: Venue
    section: Legal
    default: the state and federal courts located in New Mexico
    rationale_source: legislation
    requirement_id: REQ-labor-and-employment-law.restrictive-covenant-agreement.new-mexico.keep-clinical-health-care-agreements-under-new-mexico-law-and-forum
  - name: confidentiality_trade_secret_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of confidentiality obligations for trade secrets
    display_label: Trade Secrets Duration
    default: Perpetual
    section: Confidentiality
  - name: confidentiality_other_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of confidentiality obligations for non-trade-secret information
    display_label: Other Confidential Information Duration
    default: 24 months
    section: Confidentiality
    default_value_rationale: >-
      24 months is common for non-trade-secret confidentiality obligations in
      employment agreements. A finite term keeps the non-secret obligation from
      operating as an indirect restraint on the general skills and knowledge New
      Mexico refuses to protect.
    rationale_source: editorial
  - name: employee_nonsolicit_included
    type: boolean
    description: Whether the employee non-solicitation covenant is included
    display_label: Employee Non-Solicitation Included
    default: true
    section: Employee Non-Solicitation
  - name: employee_nonsolicit_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of employee non-solicitation restriction
    display_label: Employee Non-Solicitation Duration
    default: 12 months
    section: Employee Non-Solicitation
    default_value_rationale: >-
      12 months is a common enforceable duration and stays within the one-year
      ceiling the health-care practitioner statute preserves for employee
      non-solicits, so the same term is safe whether or not the worker is a
      covered practitioner.
    rationale_source: legislation
    requirement_id: REQ-labor-and-employment-law.restrictive-covenant-agreement.new-mexico.limit-preserved-practitioner-provisions-to-statutory-bounds
  - name: covered_employee_period
    type: string
    description: >-
      Lookback period for determining which employees are covered by the
      non-solicitation restriction.
    display_label: Covered Employee Period
    default: 12 months
    section: Employee Non-Solicitation
    default_value_rationale: >-
      12 months is the most common lookback period for employee non-solicitation
      scope.
  - name: customer_nonsolicit_included
    type: boolean
    description: Whether the customer/partner non-solicitation covenant is included
    display_label: Customer Non-Solicitation Included
    default: true
    section: Customer Non-Solicitation
  - name: customer_nonsolicit_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of customer/partner non-solicitation restriction
    display_label: Customer Non-Solicitation Duration
    default: 12 months
    section: Customer Non-Solicitation
    default_value_rationale: >-
      12 months is a common enforceable duration and stays within the one-year
      ceiling the health-care practitioner statute preserves for patient
      non-solicits.
    rationale_source: legislation
    requirement_id: REQ-labor-and-employment-law.restrictive-covenant-agreement.new-mexico.limit-preserved-practitioner-provisions-to-statutory-bounds
  - name: covered_customer_period
    type: string
    description: >-
      Lookback period for determining which customers are covered by the
      non-solicitation and non-dealing restrictions.
    display_label: Covered Customer Period
    default: 12 months
    section: Customer Non-Solicitation
    default_value_rationale: >-
      12 months is the most common lookback period for customer non-solicitation
      scope.
  - name: noncompete_included
    type: boolean
    description: >-
      Whether the non-competition covenant is included. New Mexico enforces a
      non-compete when a court deems it reasonable in time, geography, and scope
      and tied to a legitimate business interest. It is unenforceable, however,
      where it restricts a covered health-care practitioner's clinical services
      in New Mexico. This template recites the reasonableness basis and the
      practitioner exclusion when the covenant is included.
    display_label: Non-Competition Included
    default: false
    section: Non-Competition
    default_value_rationale: >-
      Conservative default. A New Mexico non-compete must be justified on the
      facts of the particular case, and no New Mexico court is obliged to narrow
      an overbroad covenant absent express contract language authorizing it.
      Include only after confirming the worker is not one of the ten covered
      health-care practitioner classes and the time, territory, and scope are
      matched to an identified protectable interest.
    rationale_source: editorial
  - name: noncompete_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of non-competition restriction
    display_label: Non-Competition Duration
    default: 12 months
    section: Non-Competition
    default_value_rationale: >-
      12 months is a common enforceable duration. New Mexico tests duration on
      the facts of the particular case with no fixed cap and no safe harbor
      so the period should be connected to the interest it protects rather than
      copied from a form.
    rationale_source: editorial
  - name: territory
    type: string
    description: Geographic scope of the non-competition restriction
    display_label: Restricted Territory
    default: the geographic area in which Employee actually worked or had material responsibility for Employer during employment
    section: Non-Competition
    default_value_rationale: >-
      Tied to where Employee actually worked rather than the employer's
      footprint. A New Mexico district court cut a one-hundred-mile dental
      restriction to thirty miles; geography sized to the worker's real
      territory is the least vulnerable to that treatment.
    rationale_source: case_law
    requirement_id: REQ-labor-and-employment-law.restrictive-covenant-agreement.new-mexico.keep-covenants-reasonable-and-tied-to-a-legitimate-interest
  - name: competitive_business_definition
    type: string
    description: >-
      Description of the business activities that constitute competition with
      the employer.
    display_label: Competitive Business
    section: Non-Competition
  - name: specified_competitors
    type: string
    description: >-
      Optional named list of specific competitors. Naming the employer's real
      competitors is strong evidence the covenant protects an identified
      interest rather than punishing departure, which is exactly the showing the
      New Mexico reasonableness test rewards.
    display_label: Specified Competitors
    default: ''
    section: Non-Competition
  - name: nondealing_included
    type: boolean
    description: Whether the no-business-with-covered-customers covenant is included.
    display_label: No Business with Covered Customers Included
    default: false
    section: No Business with Covered Customers
  - name: nondealing_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of the no-business-with-covered-customers restriction
    display_label: No Business with Covered Customers Duration
    default: 12 months
    section: No Business with Covered Customers
  - name: passive_public_holdings_threshold
    type: string
    description: >-
      Maximum ownership percentage of publicly traded securities permitted under
      the Passive Public Holdings carveout.
    display_label: Passive Public Holdings Threshold
    default: five percent
    section: Definitions
    default_value_rationale: >-
      Five percent of any class of publicly traded securities is the standard
      passive investment carveout across restrictive covenant agreements.
  - name: noninvestment_included
    type: boolean
    description: Whether the non-investment covenant is included.
    display_label: Non-Investment Included
    default: false
    section: Non-Investment
  - name: noninvestment_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of non-investment restriction
    display_label: Non-Investment Duration
    default: 12 months
    section: Non-Investment
  - name: nondisparagement_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of non-disparagement obligation (measured from termination)
    display_label: Non-Disparagement Duration
    default: 24 months
    section: Non-Disparagement
    default_value_rationale: 24 months is common for employment non-disparagement provisions.
priority_fields:
  - employer_name
  - employee_name
